Biography

After spending his first four years in the Baylor program as a tight end/inside receiver, fifth-year senior Mike Miller has moved to center for his final Green and Gold campaign. 2006: Played in all 12 games as a junior inside receiver, mainly on special teams, but did not record any statistics ... Saw action on 115 snaps to earn third Baylor letter ... Named to spring Big 12 Commissioner[apos]s Honor Roll. 2005: Appeared in all 11 games and made one start (vs. Oklahoma State) to earn his second letter ... Made lone reception, a two-yard grab, in season-finale vs. Oklahoma State ... Earned second-team Academic All-Big 12 honors ... Played 194 snaps. 2004: First-team Academic All-Big 12 selection played in all 11 games with three starts ... Tallied eight receptions for 39 yards on the season with one touchdown to earn first Baylor letter ... Made first career start against Texas State and recorded a career-high two receptions for 21 yards and a touchdown, a 2-yarder from Dane King ... Played 204 snaps ... Named to spring Big 12 Commissioner[apos]s Honor Roll. 2003: Sat out the season as a redshirt. High School: Barbe High School, Lake Charles, La. ... Two-time all-district quarterback ... Completed 79-of-146 passes for 1,403 yards and 15 touchdowns as a senior ... Also rushed for 852 yards and 13 touchdowns on 187 carries in final prep season ... Named the offensive MVP on the All-Southwest Louisiana team by the Lake Charles American Press ... Honorable mention selection to the academic all-state team ... Earned seven varsity letters -- three in football and two in both basketball and track ... Coached by Jimmy Shaver at the District 3-5A school. Personal: The son of Mike and Joyce Miller, Michael Gilpin Miller was born April 6, 1984, in Lake Charles, La. ... Sister, Lauryn, was a javelin thrower at Texas A&M from 1997 to 1999, while his uncle, Jack, was a football player at McNeese State ... Younger brother, Ryan, is a junior offensive lineman at LSU ... Entrepreneurship and professional sales major.
